Sequence Information.Peptide Name: Caerin 3.5 (UCLL1c; natural AMPs; frog, amphibians, animals; XXA)
Sequence Information.Source: skin dorsal glands, Australian dainty green tree frog, Litoria gracilenta

Literature Information.Literature: Activity: Activity against B.cereus (MIC >100 ug/ml), E.coli (MIC>100 ug/ml), L. lactis (MIC 100 uM), L.innocua (MIC >100 ug/ml), M. luteus (MIC >100 ug/ml, S.aureus ATCC 25923 (MIC >100 ug/ml), S.epidermidis (MIC >100 ug/ml), S.uberis (MIC >100 ug/ml), E.clocae (MIC >100 ug/ml), P.multocida (MIC>100 ug/ml), and P.haemolytica (MIC >100 ug/ml).Updated 5/2020, 7/2021; 12/2024
Literature Information.Author: Maclean MJ, Brinkworth CS, Bilusich D, Bowie JH, Doyle JR, Llewellyn LE, Tyler MJ2006
Literature Information.Title: New caerin antibiotic peptides from the skin secretion of the Dainty Green Tree Frog Litoria gracilenta. Identification using positive and negative ion electrospray mass spectrometry
